Ms Saryu Dave, a resident of Louis Trichardt since her marriage in 1958, passed away at the age of 82 on Wednesday, 18 May, at the Eugene Marais Hospital in Pretoria. She suffered a short illness after a fall at home. Saryu’s cremation service took place in Louis Trichardt on Thursday, 19 May. She and her husband Arvind (90) had celebrated their 64th wedding anniversary on 10 May. The Dave family thanked all the doctors, hospitals and ambulance staff who assisted in caring for Saryu during her illness. “All condolence messages and prayers during the time of bereavement are much appreciated as it gave the family strength and solace. Also a special thank you to Dove’s undertakers and the working committee of Louis Trichardt Hindu Seva Samaj in making the funeral and cremation arrangements,” said the family. Saryu is survived her husband, two sons, five grandchildren, two brothers and one sister. She will be dearly missed by her family, friends and community members. 